
Simple Usage
------------

    $ python main.py --daemon --port=11002 --db_host='db.host' --db_port=27017 \
        --db_name=blafio --db_usr=blafio --db_pwd=secret

Or you can create a configuration file `./config.py` (you can copy the sample 
and rename it), put the options in there and it all will be automatically loaded.


Requirements
------------

Python 2.6 or 2.7. Not 2.5 or below or 3.x.


Dependencies
------------

* asyncmongo
* lockfile
* mongoengine
* pymongo
* python-daemon
* redis
* tornado
* wsgiref

